column5: English Description
The first symbol from the symbol equence of a cell value is different from the first symbol in the pattern computed over all  symbol sequences of cell values in an adjacent context
The first symbol from the reversed symbol equence of a cell value is different from the first symbol in the pattern computed over all reversed symbol sequences of cell values in an adjacent context
At least two values in the adjacent cell context are not null equivalent values, and all such values have the same symbol chain, but the value in this cell does not
All cells in adjacent context (excepting cells with null or null-equivalent values) have values that are numeric, but not when this cell is added to the context

All cells in adjacent context (excepting cells with null or null-equivalent values) have values that are consistently have the same two consecutive symbols in their symbol sequence, and the first symbol is D (digit), but this does not hold when this cell is added to the context
The pattern computed over all symbol sequences of cell values in adjacent context starts with D (digit), but not when this cell is added to the context
The pattern computed over all reversed symbol sequences of cell values in adjacent context starts with D (digit), but not when this cell is added to the context

All cells in adjacent context (excepting cells with null or null-equivalent values) have values that are numeric (includes digits, decimals separated with the decimal comma or the decimal point, thousands indicated optionally with a comma, space, or point), but not when this cell is added to the context
The pattern computed over all symbol sequences of cell values in adjacent context has at least three symbols not including space, but not when this cell is added to the context
The pattern computed over all reversed symbol sequences of cell values in adjacent context has at least three symbols not including space, but not when this cell is added to the context

All cells in a context (excepting cells with null or null-equivalent values) have values that produce the same symbol set signature, and that does not include a space, but not when this cell is added to the context
The pattern computed over all  symbol sequences of cell values in an adjacent context has at least two symbols not including space, but pattern breaks when the symbol sequence of the cell is added

The pattern computed over all reversed symbol sequences of cell values in an adjacent context has at least two symbols not including space, but pattern breaks when the reversed symbol sequence of the cell is added
Cell values in column context agree on case, cell value case disagrees
Cell length<10% of min cell length in context
Cell length<30% of min cell length in context
Cell length >150% of max cell length in context
Cell length >160% of max cell length in context
Cell length >170% of max cell length in context
Cell length >180% of max cell length in context
Cell length >190% of max cell length in context
Cell context values have a consistent character count, inconsistent with the cell value, and values are not numeric.
